The national chairman, All Progressives Congress (APC) national caretaker committee, Ma Mala Buni, who is also the governor of Yobe, on Thursday held a closed-door meeting with the former interim national chairman of the party, Chief Bisi Akande. TribuneOnline authoritatively gathered that the closed-door meeting, which was held at the country home of Akande in Ila Orangun, Osun State lasted for more than one hour. Though details of the meeting were still sketchy as of the time of filing this report, our correspondent was informed that the major issue discussed centred on how to resolve the lingering crisis within the APC. ALSO READ: Buhari suspends NSITF MD, Somefun, three Executive Directors, eight others Apart from Buni, other top notchers of the APC in the meeting include the governor of Osun State, Mr Gboyega Oyetolta, who is a member of the national caretaker committee, Niger State governor, Alhaji Sanni Bello and the secretary of the committee, Senator Akpan Udo Edehe. A credible source informed our correspondent that Akande was said to have tasked the APC national caretaker committee to be fair and passionate about resolving the crises rocking the party by uniting all the feuding stakeholders and members. YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE HEADLINES FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE Court Threatens To Revoke Shehu Sani’s Bail The Federal High Court, Abuja, Monday, said it would revoke the bail granted Senator Shehu Sani if he fails to appear in court on the next adjourned date for the trial of the two-count criminal charges preferred against him by the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission… Read Full Story Buhari Appoints New Chief Personal Security Officer President Muhammadu Buhari has approved the appointment of Deputy Commissioner of Police (DCP), Aliyu Abubakar Musa, as his Chief Personal Security Officer (CPSO). He replaces Commissioner of Police (CP) Abdulkarim Dauda, who was recently redeployed… Read Full Story APC: Buni-Led Caretaker Committee Promises True Reconcili